@doc overview
@name gaiafrontend.css.Labels
@description
<p>Use these classes in order to set the displaying mode of the label control inside a form.</p>

<h2>Example</h2>
<div class="well">
    <p>
        <label class="control-label col-md-4">Texto de prueba</label>
        <br/>
    </p>
</div>
<h2>Jade</h2>
<div class="well">
    <pre>
        label.control-label.col-md-4 Texto de prueba
    </pre>
</div>
<h2>HTML</h2>
<div class="well">
    <pre>
        <label class="control-label col-md-4">Texto de prueba</label>
    </pre>
</div>
<h2>Required styles</h2>
<div class="well">
    <p>
        <code>.control-label</code>
        It's used to align inline the label control inside a form.
    <p>
     <code>.col-md-*</code>
        We have this style to define the displaying mode. In mobile devices the grid will be set in vertical mode and in PC or tablets, itÂ´s displayed horizontally. The * can be set to 1, 4, 6 or 8 values.
    <pre>
        label.control-label.col-md-*
    </pre>
</div>